gomodel:SYNGO_2459  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Domain 3 of NCAM-conjugated Covaspheres were bound to the substratecoated NCAM.\nDomain 3 of NCAM-conjugated Covaspheres were bound to substrate-coated domain 3 of NCAM protein.\nNCAM-transformed cells were attached to substrate-coated peptides.\n\n6/3/2018 Pim\n- NCAM1 is a known 'integral component of presynaptic membrane (GO:0099056)' (see ticket #2224) and integral component of postsynaptic membrane (GO:0099055) (see ticket #2406).\n-\n-. Experimental description: EXPERIMENTAL PROCEDURES\nExpression and Refolding of the Recombinant NCAM Domain 3 Protein\nThe chick NCAM cDNA fragment encoding the third Ig-like domain between amino acid positions 195 and 288 was amplified by PCR" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6194-9648" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5518-6584" ;
        dc:date           "2018-05-31" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_2459" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_9031" .

